definition.@value: Fraser syndrome is a rare syndrome characterised by cryptophthalmos and syndactyly and associated with a wide variety of other anomalies including: middle and outer ear malformations; high-arched palate; cleavage along the midplane of nares and tongue; hypertelorism; laryngeal stenosis; wide separation of symphysis pubis; displacement of umbilicus and nipples; absent or multicystic kidneys; bicornuate uterus, malformed Fallopian tubes, fusion of labia and enlargement of clitoris in girls; and undescended testes and small penis with hypospadias in boys.
